cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CV. 

The paper discusses the use of positive definite kernels and their associated Reproducing Kernel Hilbert Spaces for learning from data, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also analyzes eigenvalue decay of kernel operators and matrices, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper discusses the properties of eigenfunctions/eigenvectors and "Fourier" coefficients of functions in the kernel space, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper investigates the fitting capacity of kernels, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV).
